                    </div>
                    <span>Simply put, one of the best, if not THE best, books I have ever read on C++ (or any language).  Assumes the reader knows the basics of the language.  The writing style is engaging and witty.  The material is immediately useful in any C++ development and is quantized into easily digestible chunks.  I have been reading one or two sections ("items") each day at work.  I look forward to reading Volume 2.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Great Book!</div>
